le:Lesser magical balance built.png|280px]]\n|icon = [[File:Lesser magical balance icon.png]]\n|furniturename = Elemental balance\n|release = [[31 May]] [[2006]]\n|update = PLAYER-OWNED HOUSES!\n|level = 37\n|experience = 176\n|room = [[Games room]]\n|hotspot = [[Elemental balance space]]\n|flatpack = No\n|examine = You can practice your magic here.\n|id = 13395\n|itemid = 8156\n}}\n\nA '''lesser magical balance''' can be built in the [[Elemental balance space]] of the [[Games room]] in a [[player-owned house]]. It requires 37 [[Construction]] to build and when built, it gives 176 [[experience]]. The player must have a [[hammer]] and a [[saw]] in their inventory to build it.\n\nTo play the game, there must be two players. Each player has a turn at turning the sphere to the colour white, which means it has balanced with all of the elements. Using higher-level spells on it, such as [[Fire Wave]], will make the sphere more of the element's colour than a lower-level spell, such as [[Fire Strike]]. Using this can help in turning the sphere white. To change the sphere white, you cast the spells that begin to balance it. If it is slightly green, perhaps you should not use any [[Earth spells|Earth]]-based spells.\n\n==Mechanics==\nEach element has a colour. Air is cyan, water is blue, earth is green, fire is red. The more of an element there is, the brighter the orb will be. there are 6 levels of brightness. very slight, slight, a bit, quite, bright and glowing bright. air and earth are opposites, as are water and fire. if the ball is cyan, you can reduce its colour by casting the opposite of air, which is earth, and vice versa. the colour of the ball will be represented by which of the two pairs is strongest. A strike spell will change the colour by 1 shade, a bolt by 2, a blast by 3, a wave by 4, and a surge by 5.\n\n==Creation==\n{{Recipe\n|skill1 = Construction\n|skill1lvl = 37\n|skill1boostable = Yes\n|skill1exp = 176\n|members = Yes\n|ticks = 5\n|tools = Saw, Hammer\n|mat1 = Air rune\n|mat1quantity = 500\n|mat2 = Earth rune\n|mat2quantity = 500\n|mat3 = Fire rune\n|mat3quantity = 500\n|mat4 = Water rune\n|mat4quantity = 500\n|output1 = Lesser magical balance\n|output1pic = Lesser magical balance icon\n|output1cost = 0\n}}\n\n{{Games room}}"}